---

## **🎯 OBJECTIVE**

**Goal**: Create TRUE Web4 component architecture while preserving working ServerHierarchyManager methods

**Pragmatic Approach**:
- ✅ Extract proven methods from ServerHierarchyManager
- ✅ Distribute methods to proper component classes
- ✅ Keep all working logic unchanged
- ✅ Add proper models (HTTPSServerModel, RouterModel, etc.)
- ✅ Get rid of functional patterns → Radical OOP
- ✅ Each class as own component (splinter-ready)

**Anti-Pattern to Eliminate**:
```typescript
// ❌ ServerHierarchyManager: functional mess (1500+ lines, mixed concerns)
class ServerHierarchyManager {
  private serverModel: ONCEServerModel;
  private httpServer?: Server;           // HTTP concern
  private wsServer?: WebSocketServer;    // WebSocket concern
  private serverRegistry: Map<...>;      // Registry concern
  private browserClients: Set<...>;      // Client concern
  
  async startServer() { ... }            // 100 lines
  handleHttpRequest() { ... }            // 200 lines (switch/case)
  handleWebSocket() { ... }              // 150 lines
  registerWithPrimary() { ... }          // 50 lines
  performHousekeeping() { ... }          // 80 lines
}
```

**Target Architecture**:
```typescript
// ✅ Proper component separation
ONCE (kernel)
  → DefaultHTTPSServer (HTTP/HTTPS + routing)
    → DefaultRouter (dynamic routing)
      → DefaultRoute[] (individual routes)
    → DefaultLetsEncrypt (certificate management)
  → DefaultWebSocketServer (WebSocket handling)
  → DefaultPrimaryServer (registry + housekeeping)
  → DefaultClientServer (registration)
```

